27/03/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- The leader of the Socialist Movement for Integration (SMI), Ilir Meta, sent a request to parliament Wednesday (March 26th) seeking establishment of a panel to investigate the March 15th blasts at the munitions depot in Gerdec .They killed at least 24 people and injured hundreds more. The SMI says the commission should investigate conditions at military munitions sites across the country. The request was approved despite opposition from some rightist parties in parliament. (Shekulli, Shqip, Koha Jone - 27/03/08; BalkanWeb, Top-Channel - 26/03/08)
